label.name: Name
label.select-provider: Select the provider you want to connect with
label.extension-email-explaination: This email address is used for voicemail and CRM integration.
label.no-trunk-description: This extension will not be able to make outgoing calls.
label.no-trunks-available-description: Create a trunk first to enable outgoing calls for this extension.
label.extensions-instructions-1: You can connect to an extension using a SIP client like MicroSIP or Zoiper. Alternatively, you can use a physical IP phone. Use the following settings to configure your SIP client or IP phone:
label.extensions-instructions-2: After configurating your SIP client or IP phone, it will show up here as connected.
label.extension-general-description: This section is enough to start using the extension in an IP Phone or Softphone.
label.no-ongoing-calls: There are no ongoing calls at the moment
label.table-live-data: The data in this table is live
label.ringall-description: All extensions are rang, and the first one to pick up gets connected.
label.rrmemory-description: Iterates over the extensions, and remembers where it left off when another call comes in.
label.rrordered-description: Iterates over the extensions, but always starts at the first in the list.
label.fewestcalls-description: Connects to the extension that has answered the fewest calls
label.trunks-instructions-1: A SIP Trunk is used to connect your PBX with the internet. This allows extensions to make outbound calls.
label.trunks-instructions-2: In order to use this, you need an account from a SIP provider. Your provider will provide you with a host, username and password.
label.trunks-instructions-3: If the connection with your provider was successful, it will show a green dot in the table to the left.
label.ignore-call-description: Your provider will return to the caller that this number is not in use.
label.ring-all-extensions-description: The extension that picks up first will get connected
label.cid-explanation: Note: Some providers will ignore this, and always overwrite your outgoing Caller ID
label.transfer-to-queue: Transfer the call to a queue
label.dtmf-menu-description: Play a message, and let the caller press a key on their dialpad

message.delete-extension-confirmation: Are you sure you want to delete this extension?
message.delete-queue-confirmation: Are you sure you want to delete this queue?
message.delete-trunk-confirmation: Are you sure you want to delete this trunk?
